“I was very impressed. She has achieved something good,” he said. His daughter, Dr Vuyo Lindelwe Mthethwa, graduated with a PhD in Education on Tuesday. Her thesis focused on students’ participation in university governance, and their academic experiences in select South African universities. She said: “After a protracted struggle against colonialism and apartheid, South Africa’s higher education has now achieved full student participation in university governance.” She found four critical issues compounding the intersection: political accountability, the nature of academic experiences, students’ expectations of lecturers and students’ economic circumstances. Judge Tshabalala said he was proud of his daughter’s choice of field of study. “It’s education, which is good. “It deals with the current situation,” he said. Daily News